- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses the use of bank statement data in credit scoring, which has implications for the societal impact of credit scoring models. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper may touch on issues related to data privacy and security, as it involves the use of sensitive financial data. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper may involve techniques related to information retrieval, as the bank statement data needs to be processed and analyzed to extract relevant features. 
- cs.DB (Databases): The paper may involve techniques related to database management, as the bank statement data needs to be stored and queried for feature extraction.
